HEADWORD: Satanical
<hw>Sa*tan"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>satanique</ets>,
Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Satan; having the qualities of
Satan; resembling Satan; extremely malicious or wicked; devilish;
infernal.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Satanic</xex> strength.⟦rdquo⟧
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Satanic</xex> host.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Detest the slander which, with a <qex>Satanic</qex> smile, exults
over the character it has ruined.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. T.
Dwight.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sa*tan"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sa*tan"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
